INUMBER 1669
NAME 298
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
MISC
*DESCRIPTION_START
You gaze into the lens...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
	IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
		RANDOM INTNUM83 1 1000 1
		EQUAL ITEMVAL3 INTNUM83
		ECHO PLAYER As you touch the lens of worlds for the first time, a pulse of energy pass between you and it. You sense that some of your life-essence has joined with the object.
		PLREVENT 1
		CONTPLREVENT
		ECHO PLAYER "Beware, disciple. Never share your lens with any other -- never allow another to touch it!  The energy in this lens contains a part of you, and should another touch it, the lens will be destroyed along with that part of you... Keep it well. There are more tests ahead."
		PLREVENT 1
		CONTPLREVENT
		ECHO PLAYER "You have done well, disciple. Return in one hour and we shall be ready with our decision to admit you into the Fold."
    EQUAL INTNUM84 888
;		ECHO PLAYER "If you someday travel the planes beyond Andor, you will be confronted by creatures of incredible power. It would be folly to travel there if you are not prepared to hold your own in battle with them. Next, you must prove your skill as a warrior."
;   PLREVENT 1
;   CONTPLREVENT
;   ECHO PLAYER "Travel to the summit of the highest mountain in what you know as the Teeth of Shartan. There, you will be confronted by two servitors of the outer planes. You must defeat them in battle. You may bring allies if you wish, but be warned!  You must deliver the final strike!"
	ENDIF
	IFVERB EXAMINE -1
