;
;
;                       CRYSTAL HEART
INUMBER 567
NAME 904
WEIGHT 10
VOLUME 3
PARAMETER1 2
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 ! 77
	EQUAL ITEMADJ3 77
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMVAL2 ! 6
	EQUAL ITEMVAL2 6
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You see a rounded lump of blue-white crystal matter which glimmers faintly
	ECHO PLAYER with a unique luminescence. It is about the same size as both of your fists
	ECHO PLAYER held together, and nearly the same shape. Within its substance, you notice,
	ECHO PLAYER there are channels... veins and arteries, you suppose. These channels, or
	ECHO PLAYER the clear fluid within them, are the source of the heart's glow.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB EAT -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER Perhaps drinking out of it would be a better idea... you can't chew crystal.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DRINK -1
	ECHO OTHERS %N tips back %h head, drinking deeply from %a.
	ECHO PLAYER You tip back your head, drinking the clear fluid from within the heart.
	IFVAR DANHEART ! TIM
		EQUAL DANHEART TIM
		SPELL 105 50
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
	ECHO PLAYER You gently push the heart, causing it to throb.
	ECHO OTHERS %A throbs.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
	RANDOM DUMMY1 1 500 100
	STRCVT 0 DUMMY1
	STRCVT 1 STR
	ECHO PLAYER You try to pry the heart open.
	IFVAR DUMMY1 > STR
		ECHO PLAYER [Strength: %1, Roll: %0] You nearly shatter the heart, but you aren't quite strong enough.
		ECHO OTHERS %N tries to pry %a apart.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR DUMMY1 <= STR
		ECHO PLAYER [Strength: %1, Roll: %0] Success! The heart is shattered into a million tiny pieces!
		ECHO OTHERS %N pries open %a, shattering it into a million tiny pieces!
		APPEAR %S seems to be covered in a thin layer of clear, oily fluid.
		REMOVEITEM -1
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
	ECHO PLAYER You gaze into the crystalline structure of the heart.
	ECHO OTHERS %N gazes deep into the crystalline structure of %a.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
	ECHO PLAYER You turn the heart over in your hands wonderingly.
	ECHO OTHERS %N turns %a over in %h hands wonderingly.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DESTROY -1
	ECHO PLAYER You notice that the crystalline structure of the heart is nearly impervious to any assault from the outside. Perhaps if you tried to pry it open...
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
